Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees and bring 500ml of @water{500%ml} to the boil
in a #pot{} on high heat.

Peel the @carrots{3} and chop off the tops and bottoms. Quarter each carrot
lengthways and then cut each length in half. Pop the carrots into a #bowl{} and
season with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Sprinkle over the @chermoula spice mix{2%tsp} and add
@oil{1%tbsp}. Mix well to make sure the carrots are nicely coated in the spice
mix. Transfer to a #baking tray{} lined with baking paper and roast the carrots
for ~{25%minutes} on the middle shelf of your oven.

Add the @cinnamon stick{1} and @vegetable stock pot{1} to the pot of boiling
water and then pour in the @freekeh{1%cup}. Reduce the heat to medium-low and
cook for ~{10%minutes}. When the freekeh is cooked, drain into a #sieve{},
discard the cinnamon stick and leave to cool for ~{5%minutes}.

Chop off the tip of the @cucumber{1/2} and quarter it lengthways. Scrape the
seeds off with a #spoon{} and discard. Cut each strip into 1cm pieces. Pop the
cut cucumber into a bowl and season with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Sprinkle in the
@white wine vinegar{1%tbsp} and mix well.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{5%stalks}(roughly chopped),
@coriander{5%sprigs}(roughly chopped) and @mint{5%sprigs}(roughly chopped).
Mix the chopped herbs with your cucumber. Roughly chop the
@pistachios{25} and set aside.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have
one!) Mix the garlic into the @Greek style natural yoghurt{1%cup} with the
@sumac{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{pinch}.

When the freekeh has cooled slightly, mix in the cucumber and herbs. Add the
zest and juice of half the @lemon{1/2}(zested and juiced), then taste and add
more lemon juice to taste. Add more salt and @ground black pepper{} if necessary.

When your carrots are cooked and tender, serve on top of a bed of the freekeh
and finish with a sprinkle of pistachios and some dollops of your sumac
yoghurt. Yum!

> The carrot, often seen as a very everyday veggie, is the hero of this dish with its flamboyant orangeness and vitamin C. This dish is an absolute hero - it's freekeh awesome!